{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-js","path":"/posts/py-installation","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"d41b35a6-fba5-5a29-9210-29edb02c25ee","html":"<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#installing-python\">Installing Python</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#choosing-an-editor\">Choosing an editor</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#hello-world\">Hello World</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#related\">Related</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Python is an interpreted programming language that was released by Guido van Rossum in 1991. Python’s syntax and dynamic typing makes it easier to learn than other languages. In this tutorial we will tackle on how to install Python.</p>\n<h2 id=\"installing-python\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#installing-python\" aria-label=\"installing python permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Installing Python</h2>\n<p>To install python follow the instructions below:</p>\n<p>NOTE: If you have already installed Visual Studio from the <a href=\"/posts/cpp-hello-world\">C++ Tutorial</a>, then you might have\nalready installed Python. You can check it by looking at the start menu. If you see a Python 3.x folder then you don’t need to follow the instructions below.</p>\n<ol>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.python.org/downloads/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Download the latest version of Python for your platform.</a></li>\n<li>Run the downloaded installer. You will be greeted by this window.\n<span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 666px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/b2cb3d6ab3933e8c49324866e7ace1e7/ace37/screenshot-py-installation-1.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 61.66666666666666%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/b2cb3d6ab3933e8c49324866e7ace1e7/8ac56/screenshot-py-installation-1.webp 240w,\n/static/b2cb3d6ab3933e8c49324866e7ace1e7/d3be9/screenshot-py-installation-1.webp 480w,\n/static/b2cb3d6ab3933e8c49324866e7ace1e7/be082/screenshot-py-installation-1.webp 666w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 666px) 100vw, 666px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/b2cb3d6ab3933e8c49324866e7ace1e7/8ff5a/screenshot-py-installation-1.png 240w,\n/static/b2cb3d6ab3933e8c49324866e7ace1e7/e85cb/screenshot-py-installation-1.png 480w,\n/static/b2cb3d6ab3933e8c49324866e7ace1e7/ace37/screenshot-py-installation-1.png 666w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 666px) 100vw, 666px\"\n          type=\"image/png\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          src=\"/static/b2cb3d6ab3933e8c49324866e7ace1e7/ace37/screenshot-py-installation-1.png\"\n          alt=\"Python installer, check add to PATH\"\n          title=\"Python installer, check add to PATH\"\n          loading=\"lazy\"\n          style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></li>\n<li>Check the box labeled <strong>Add Python 3.x to PATH</strong>.</li>\n<li>Wait for the installation to finish, restart your computer when prompted.\n<span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 666px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/084cf144bd5c8bf48dc1e51d44aca31b/ace37/screenshot-py-installation-2.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 61.66666666666666%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/084cf144bd5c8bf48dc1e51d44aca31b/8ac56/screenshot-py-installation-2.webp 240w,\n/static/084cf144bd5c8bf48dc1e51d44aca31b/d3be9/screenshot-py-installation-2.webp 480w,\n/static/084cf144bd5c8bf48dc1e51d44aca31b/be082/screenshot-py-installation-2.webp 666w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 666px) 100vw, 666px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/084cf144bd5c8bf48dc1e51d44aca31b/8ff5a/screenshot-py-installation-2.png 240w,\n/static/084cf144bd5c8bf48dc1e51d44aca31b/e85cb/screenshot-py-installation-2.png 480w,\n/static/084cf144bd5c8bf48dc1e51d44aca31b/ace37/screenshot-py-installation-2.png 666w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 666px) 100vw, 666px\"\n          type=\"image/png\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          src=\"/static/084cf144bd5c8bf48dc1e51d44aca31b/ace37/screenshot-py-installation-2.png\"\n          alt=\"Wait for installation to finish\"\n          title=\"Wait for installation to finish\"\n          loading=\"lazy\"\n          style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></li>\n</ol>\n<h2 id=\"choosing-an-editor\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#choosing-an-editor\" aria-label=\"choosing an editor permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Choosing an editor</h2>\n<p>After setting up Python, you can choose a text editor. For the purposes of this tutorial, you can choose from these three text editors.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>IDLE - built-in with python, requires no further installation</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.jetbrains.com/pycharm/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">PyCharm</a> - an integrated development environment (IDE), this will give you a similar experience to Visual Studio. <a href=\"https://www.jetbrains.com/help/pycharm/installation-guide.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Set up PyCharm by following the instructions on their page.</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://code.visualstudio.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Visual Studio Code (vscode)</a> - this is different from plain Visual Studio, vscode is more of a text editor with support for extensions rather than an IDE</li>\n</ul>\n<p>For this tutorial, we’ll only use IDLE as it takes little time to set up.</p>\n<h2 id=\"hello-world\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#hello-world\" aria-label=\"hello world permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Hello World</h2>\n<p>You can open IDLE by looking for the Python folder in the start menu or searching for it. Once opened it should look like this.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 671px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/bfaab4f650b159d6a36f37c62b64208b/d0e73/screenshot-py-installation-3.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 106.25%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/bfaab4f650b159d6a36f37c62b64208b/8ac56/screenshot-py-installation-3.webp 240w,\n/static/bfaab4f650b159d6a36f37c62b64208b/d3be9/screenshot-py-installation-3.webp 480w,\n/static/bfaab4f650b159d6a36f37c62b64208b/86a29/screenshot-py-installation-3.webp 671w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 671px) 100vw, 671px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/bfaab4f650b159d6a36f37c62b64208b/8ff5a/screenshot-py-installation-3.png 240w,\n/static/bfaab4f650b159d6a36f37c62b64208b/e85cb/screenshot-py-installation-3.png 480w,\n/static/bfaab4f650b159d6a36f37c62b64208b/d0e73/screenshot-py-installation-3.png 671w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 671px) 100vw, 671px\"\n          type=\"image/png\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          src=\"/static/bfaab4f650b159d6a36f37c62b64208b/d0e73/screenshot-py-installation-3.png\"\n          alt=\"IDLE Python interactive shell\"\n          title=\"IDLE Python interactive shell\"\n          loading=\"lazy\"\n          style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>This window is only an interactive shell, you can’t edit and save your code here. To enter the editor and create a new file, go to File > New File or press <code class=\"language-text\">CTRL + N</code>. An untitled window should pop up.</p>\n<p>Hello world in Python can be written in just one line like so</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"python\"><pre class=\"language-python\"><code class=\"language-python\"><span class=\"token keyword\">print</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"Hello world!\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Save your code by going to File > Save or <code class=\"language-text\">CTRL + S</code>. After saving you can now run it by going to Run > Run Module or <code class=\"language-text\">F5</code>. You should see the output back at the interactive shell.</p>\n<h2 id=\"related\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#related\" aria-label=\"related permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Related:</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"/posts/cpp-hello-world\">C++ - Hello World</a></li>\n</ul>","fields":{"slug":"/posts/py-installation","tagSlugs":["/tag/python/","/tag/tutorial/","/tag/install/","/tag/introduction/","/tag/hello-world/"]},"frontmatter":{"date":"2020-10-06T16:25:03+08:00","description":"Python is an interpreted programming language that was released by Guido van Rossum in 1991. Python's syntax and dynamic typing makes it easier to learn than other languages. In this tutorial we will tackle on how to install Python.","tags":["Python","Tutorial","Install","Introduction","Hello World"],"title":"Python Installation and Hello World","socialImage":null}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/posts/py-installation"}},"staticQueryHashes":["251939775","3942705351","401334301"]}